{"petition_id":1219175,"title":"Wal-Mart Kemptville, Ontario: Give Carla Cheney her job back, fired for saving a dog left in a hot car.","status":"open","url":"http://api.change.org/petitions/wal-mart-kemptville-ontario-give-carla-cheney-her-job-back-fired-for-saving-a-dog-left-in-a-hot-car","overview":"<p><span>Under the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/statutes/english/elaws_statutes_90o36_e.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ontario SPCA Act</a><span>&nbsp;it is illegal for a pet owner to leave an animal in a parked car if the temperature could endanger its life. According to the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://ottawahumane.ca/your-pets/toohot.cfm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ottawa Humane Society</a><span>, even moderately warm outdoor temperatures can quickly become sweltering for dogs on the inside of a parked car. &nbsp;The site adds that dogs are particularly susceptible to high temperatures, and that a temperature of 104&deg; F could prove fatal within a few minutes. Yet Wal-Mart employee Carla Cheney was fired because she called the police to report a dog left in a car on such a hot day.</span></p>\r\n<p>By firing an employee for taking an action that was in the public interest, Wal-Mart sets a dangerous precedent when it comes to employees reporting / acting in the best interests of the general public.</p>\r\n<p>Reinstate Carla, and review your policies company-wide that would rather fire someone than have them save a life.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Full story here:</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ibtimes.com/carla-cheney-fired-kemptville-wal-mart-calling-police-customer-who-left-dog-hot-car-1342005\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ibtimes.com/carla-cheney-fired-kemptville-wal-mart-calling-police-customer-who-left-dog-hot-car-1342005</a></p>","targets":[{"name":"Wal-Mart Human Resources, Corporate Affairs Canada, Wal-Mart","title":"Corporate Affairs Canada, Wal-Mart","type":"custom"}],"letter_body":"Give Car